- Yeah.

40:17.640 --> 40:20.314
I gotta be transferred
to protective custody first.

40:21.640 --> 40:23.438
This what you want to do?

40:24.560 --> 40:26.791
I don't want to...

40:26.960 --> 40:28.713
...but I will.

40:40.160 --> 40:41.799
Hello?

40:52.160 --> 40:55.392
- No one's supposed to be in here.
- Oh. Oh, I'm sorry. I'm... I'm...

40:55.560 --> 40:57.870
I'm an attorney here, and I was looking...

40:58.560 --> 41:01.280
...for Mr. Pierce.
I wanted to talk to him about this case.

41:01.440 --> 41:05.400
He's in depositions all day. Mr. Salinas
is supervising attorney in his absence.

41:06.800 --> 41:09.759
- You'll have to leave.
- I'm sorry.

41:11.480 --> 41:14.120
I don't know why
they sent me this. I need more than this.

41:14.320 --> 41:16.710
- That's all we got.
- I don't want the summary.

41:16.880 --> 41:19.270
- I want the full deposition here.
- Okay.

41:19.440 --> 41:21.352
And what about tomorrow?
What's my agenda?

41:21.520 --> 41:23.477
- You're downtown all day.
- What is first?

41:23.640 --> 41:27.270
- Mr. Rutner at 9 a. m.
- I don't want to meet with him.

41:39.000 --> 41:41.231
<i>- Hello?
- Uh, hello.</i>

41:41.400 --> 41:43.312
My name is Roman J. Israel, Esquire...

41:43.520 --> 41:46.194
...from the law offices of George Pierce.

41:46.360 --> 41:48.511
I represent Derrell Ellerbee.

41:48.680 --> 41:51.798
I'd like to speak to ADA Kate Becker.

41:51.960 --> 41:53.553
<i>Speaking.</i>

41:54.880 --> 41:57.952
Oh. Oh, okay. Uh, sorry.

41:58.160 --> 41:59.389
<i>- Uh, hi.
- Hi.</i>

41:59.560 --> 42:02.678
My client, Mr. Derrell Ellerbee...

42:02.840 --> 42:06.470
...is interested in discussing a deal.

42:06.640 --> 42:08.996
I have 40 open cases, so refresh me.

42:09.160 --> 42:10.594
<i>Right. Uh, uh, uh...</i>

42:11.320 --> 42:13.915
Convenience-store shooting. Um...

42:14.080 --> 42:17.710
An Armenian man was killed,
and, uh, there's a reward offered?

42:18.040 --> 42:19.554
Mm-hm. Okay, I have it.

42:19.760 --> 42:20.830
<i>The shooter...</i>

42:21.800 --> 42:24.520
...in this case, is a fugitive...

42:24.680 --> 42:26.160
...Carter Johnson.

42:26.320 --> 42:30.917
My client may know his whereabouts
and might be willing to testify.

42:31.480 --> 42:33.915
- He'll deliver on that?
- Well, that depends.

42:34.080 --> 42:38.074
If you waive all objections and appeal,
and he's willing to cooperate...

42:38.280 --> 42:40.078
...we'll drop the assault and kidnapping.

42:40.280 --> 42:43.796
<i>And we'll reduce murder one
to manslaughter, voluntary, 10 years.</i>

42:43.960 --> 42:45.599
Involuntary, three to five.

42:45.760 --> 42:48.832
No, a 21-year-old clerk was killed
in the commission of a robbery.

42:49.040 --> 42:50.269
It won't happen.

42:50.440 --> 42:54.912
Well, my client is giving you
the whole case at a great risk to himself.

42:55.080 --> 42:57.436
<i>- Let's discuss mitigating circumstances.
- Let's not.</i>

42:57.600 --> 43:00.911
Voluntary manslaughter, 10 years.
It's a good deal.

43:01.520 --> 43:03.159
It's an enema of sunshine.

43:03.520 --> 43:04.920
I don't have time for this.

43:05.080 --> 43:07.231
Well, I'm sorry for taking a nanosecond...

43:07.400 --> 43:09.915
...off of your assembly-line,
rubber-stamp existence.

43:10.080 --> 43:12.072
The People withdraw their offer.

43:12.240 --> 43:14.994
I don't care what the... Hello?

43:39.200 --> 43:40.919
Hi.

43:42.080 --> 43:43.833
- Hi.
- Hey.

43:44.000 --> 43:46.231
You didn't want to park closer?
There are spaces.

43:46.400 --> 43:48.596
No, I don't have a car.

43:48.760 --> 43:50.433
Wow, that's gotta be tough in L. A.

43:50.600 --> 43:53.479
I've always imagined life with one.

43:53.640 --> 43:55.950
- Thanks for doing this.
- Oh, you're welcome.

43:56.120 --> 44:01.070
Public speaking is something
I'm usually encouraged to avoid.

44:02.600 --> 44:05.240
So in anticipation of Tuesday's protest...

44:05.400 --> 44:08.313
...I've invited attorney...

44:08.480 --> 44:10.551
...Roman Israel...

44:11.000 --> 44:14.755
...to talk about our rights
and what to expect if you are arrested.

44:15.160 --> 44:16.310
Roman.

44:16.480 --> 44:17.516
Thank you.

44:23.560 --> 44:25.472
All right. Uh...

44:27.160 --> 44:29.550
Back to my beginnings.

44:30.200 --> 44:33.716
It, uh, feels good.

44:36.440 --> 44:40.354
Hell, that was 40 years ago.
So here we go. We're gonna...

44:40.760 --> 44:42.592
We're gonna rap...
I don't mean hip-hop.

44:45.160 --> 44:48.836
...a little while about
some good old-fashioned...

44:49.520 --> 44:52.991
...grassroots, in-your-face protesting.

44:54.360 --> 44:57.637
The time has come
to put social revolution...

44:58.240 --> 45:01.278
...squarely back on the agenda...

45:01.640 --> 45:03.279
...where it belongs.

45:04.400 --> 45:06.073
Look at you.

45:09.160 --> 45:11.152
Just like I was.

45:12.320 --> 45:17.031
Just starting out your fight against the...

45:17.800 --> 45:20.315
...dominant tendencies of our society.

45:20.480 --> 45:21.914
Well...

45:22.400 --> 45:24.869
...you better get ready
for the commitment it takes...

45:25.040 --> 45:27.509
...to lead a resistant lifestyle.

45:27.680 --> 45:29.558
You better start forging...

45:29.720 --> 45:32.997
...the armor to withstand the temptation...

45:33.160 --> 45:36.392
...and the financial and emotional toll.

45:36.920 --> 45:39.071
Because when it comes
to social injustice...

45:39.240 --> 45:41.232
...and judicial indifference...

45:41.400 --> 45:43.278
...and institutional racism...

45:43.440 --> 45:45.272
...and outright goddamn greed...

45:45.440 --> 45:49.593
...the overwhelming majority of the people
in this countryjust don't give a damn.

45:49.760 --> 45:51.717
- That's right.
- That's right.

45:52.240 --> 45:54.550
Civil or uncivil disobedience.

45:54.720 --> 45:57.758
The First Amendment to protect
your right to freedom of speech...

45:57.920 --> 46:02.039
...as long as you don't incite violence
or law-breaking.

46:02.200 --> 46:04.635
There will be people
that get caught up in the march.

46:04.800 --> 46:07.156
They're gonna vandalize.
Sorry. Excuse me.

46:07.320 --> 46:08.640
I see two sisters standing.

46:09.320 --> 46:11.789
Why are the sisters standing
and the brothers sitting?

46:13.120 --> 46:14.634
If we want to sit, we can ask.

46:14.800 --> 46:16.996
You ladies gotta speak up for yourselves.

46:17.160 --> 46:18.879
This ain't 40 years ago.

46:19.400 --> 46:22.791
There's no statute of limitations
on chivalry.

46:22.960 --> 46:25.600
- That's gendered and sexist.
- And polite.

46:25.800 --> 46:27.871
- And patronizing.
- And polite.

46:28.320 --> 46:29.879
What kind of law do you practice?

46:32.840 --> 46:35.833
I'm a criminal-defense attorney.

46:36.000 --> 46:38.117
Ever represent
domestic-violence defendants?

46:38.280 --> 46:39.475
Many times.

46:39.880 --> 46:42.031
- Knowing that they're guilty?
- Meaning what?

46:42.200 --> 46:43.680
Meaning you have a choice.

46:43.840 --> 46:46.833
Watch it. Someday you may need
the Sixth Amendment.

46:47.000 --> 46:48.354
Oh, that's lawyer talk.

46:49.520 --> 46:52.718
Oh, I see. So we got a Sarah Lawrence
soul sister in the band.

46:53.120 --> 46:55.794
- Ha-ha. I'm not your sister, asshole.
- Oh, whoa, whoa.

46:56.040 --> 46:58.475
- I'm not an asshole, sister.
- Hey, fuck you, brother.

47:00.160 --> 47:02.629
Settle down, okay? Thank you, Roman.

47:02.840 --> 47:04.957
- Okay.
- Did you bring something to help?

47:06.840 --> 47:08.274
Roman.

47:08.440 --> 47:09.954
Roman.

47:12.640 --> 47:15.075
I feel like I need to apologize for that.

47:15.240 --> 47:17.118
You don't. It's my fault. I say things.

47:17.280 --> 47:19.511
- Are you okay?
- No, I... Yeah, it's okay.

47:20.160 --> 47:21.480
It just got out of hand.

47:21.640 --> 47:24.553
My meanings seem to obfuscate
more than clarify.

47:24.720 --> 47:26.996
I mean, that's what the discourse is.

47:27.160 --> 47:29.038
- It's changed over the years.
- Right.

47:29.240 --> 47:30.560
- It's what we talked about.
- You did.

47:30.720 --> 47:34.191
- That's a lot of what this is about.
- I just can't seem to remove myself...

47:34.360 --> 47:37.398
...from what's happened in my life. I...

47:38.120 --> 47:39.679
This is where we are,
the way the world is.

47:39.840 --> 47:43.356
And I didn't even want to come out.
The nuns said I was a forceps baby.

47:44.680 --> 47:46.911
- Me too.
- Yeah?

47:47.080 --> 47:48.434
- No.
- No?

47:48.600 --> 47:50.432
Heh-heh. No.

48:03.560 --> 48:05.153
Is he okay?

48:06.080 --> 48:08.276
- I don't feel anything.
- Check his neck.

48:13.080 --> 48:14.753
No.

48:30.360 --> 48:31.510
What happened?

48:32.200 --> 48:35.989
- We just found him. I think he's dead.
- All right, don't touch anything.

48:37.160 --> 48:39.959
Man down, black male, 60 years of age.

48:40.120 --> 48:42.999
Not responding. Request RA.

48:44.000 --> 48:46.037
- What did I just say?
- He doesn't have ID.

48:46.200 --> 48:48.192
- What did you put in there?
- My card.

48:48.400 --> 48:50.119
Take it out.

48:50.320 --> 48:51.913
Well, without ID...

48:52.080 --> 48:54.720
...he'll get cremated and mixed up
with 1000 other homeless people.

48:54.880 --> 48:56.394
Take it out.

48:56.920 --> 48:59.640
It's just my name and number
for the coroner to call me.

48:59.800 --> 49:01.917
- Did you hear my partner?
- Okay.

49:02.560 --> 49:04.791
- Do what they say.
- I want to pay for the burial.

49:05.000 --> 49:07.390
- I'm not telling you again.
- I won't let him get swallowed up.

49:07.560 --> 49:09.517
I won't let him disappear,
completely forgotten.

49:09.680 --> 49:11.353
He most certainly was somebody.

49:30.520 --> 49:34.116
<i>All units.
Possible 187. Suspect there now.</i>

49:34.320 --> 49:36.630
<i>Western and Third
at Chinatown Express.</i>

49:36.800 --> 49:39.599
<i>Suspects are two male Hispanics.
Number one, large build...</i>

49:39.760 --> 49:41.353
I'm sorry.

49:42.560 --> 49:45.632
- What? That was unbelievable.
- I thought he had no pulse.

49:45.800 --> 49:47.792
- No one does that.
- Yeah, for good reason.

49:52.040 --> 49:53.997
Hey. Yeah, I stepped out.

49:54.160 --> 49:56.675
I'll be right back.

49:58.040 --> 50:00.077
- I have to get back.
- Yeah. Okay.

50:01.960 --> 50:05.032
- I'm gonna call you.
- Yeah, thank you. Me too.

50:28.840 --> 50:30.479
We have a problem.

50:32.520 --> 50:34.079
Come in.

50:36.040 --> 50:37.759
Close the door.

50:42.840 --> 50:45.230
Where did you get the idea
you could try and negotiate a plea?

50:45.680 --> 50:47.637
Who told you you could do that?

50:47.800 --> 50:50.679
To just ignore
what I emphatically told you?

50:51.360 --> 50:54.797
Derrell Ellerbee was stabbed and killed
this morning in general lockup.

50:54.960 --> 50:57.839
His aunt told me that Derrell requested
protective custody last night...

50:58.000 --> 50:59.912
...but was delayed
because the prosecutor said...

51:00.080 --> 51:02.436
...you pissed on her deal, Roman.

51:02.600 --> 51:05.752
That offer should, by law, have been
presented to the client, which it was not.

51:05.920 --> 51:08.435
As of now, you've exposed us
to a malpractice suit...

51:08.600 --> 51:11.354
...Roman, I would kill
to be on the other side of.

51:11.520 --> 51:16.151
You've had difficulty comprehending
my meaning, so I'll be very, very clear.

51:16.320 --> 51:19.040
As much as I wanna fire you, I can't,
as that could be construed...

51:19.200 --> 51:23.080
...as acknowledgment of wrongdoing.
So I'm gonna retain you, Roman.

51:23.760 --> 51:26.594
I'm gonna retain you,
and then I'm gonna fire you.

51:26.760 --> 51:28.592
If you attempt to quit
or you stop coming in...

51:28.760 --> 51:30.797
...I swear to God, I'll hit you
with a motion to recoup damages...

51:30.960 --> 51:32.633
...and I'll have you disbarred.

51:34.360 --> 51:36.113
We're done here.

51:58.840 --> 52:00.194
Yo, hey, man. Hey.

52:00.360 --> 52:03.671
Yo, man, I'm sorry
to bother you, man, but...

52:03.840 --> 52:05.638
Maybe you can help me out
with money or some...

52:05.800 --> 52:08.190
I mean, anything.
Look, you see where I'm at, man.

52:08.360 --> 52:10.317
All right.
Slow down, slow down, slow down.

52:10.520 --> 52:11.874
Okay, man. I'm sorry.

52:12.040 --> 52:14.874
Look, I appreciate it, man.
Look, I know it's late.

52:15.040 --> 52:18.636
- I appreciate you helping me. Cool, man.
- Here's a couple tickets for the mission.

52:19.680 --> 52:21.273
Give me the iPod, man!

52:24.520 --> 52:26.637
- Give it to me. Come on.
- Get off me.

52:27.280 --> 52:28.839
- The iPod!
- I don't have any money!

52:29.040 --> 52:30.713
- Come on!
- You got the wrong guy!

52:30.880 --> 52:33.520
You got the wrong guy!

52:47.960 --> 52:50.270
You got the wrong guy.

53:25.360 --> 53:26.794
What?

53:31.560 --> 53:32.914
What?

54:20.400 --> 54:21.470
Well, well.

54:22.600 --> 54:25.752
Come over and sit.
He'll be glad you're here.

54:25.920 --> 54:29.391
- He's awake?
- No, but I believe somewhere he knows.

54:30.440 --> 54:33.080
He was so very fond of you.

54:34.680 --> 54:36.080
He looks a lot worse.

54:36.240 --> 54:38.072
It won't be long now.

54:38.240 --> 54:41.870
Last ripple of a mighty wave
washed ashore here.

54:42.200 --> 54:44.237
And left us high and dry.

54:44.400 --> 54:47.393
No, he didn't leave us.
He'll never leave us.

54:48.280 --> 54:52.320
I thought it was built on good ground...

54:53.160 --> 54:55.675
- ...but there's nothing under it.
- Roman, what's wrong?

54:57.560 --> 54:59.836
You're too near me to hear me.

55:00.480 --> 55:02.199
Can't you see? It's clear as crystal.

55:02.400 --> 55:04.471
- What?
- We filed the wrong brief...

55:04.640 --> 55:08.316
- ...in the wrong court to the wrong judge.
- What are you talking about?

55:08.480 --> 55:10.790
A world where everyone's feelings
are reciprocated.

55:10.960 --> 55:14.271
The capacity for everyone
to contribute. Come on.

55:16.320 --> 55:18.755
Freedom is something
you can only give yourself.

55:18.960 --> 55:20.440
That's nothing he agreed with.

55:20.600 --> 55:24.116
I don't have any time anymore.
I don't have time to waste.

55:24.280 --> 55:25.839
Trying to...

55:26.400 --> 55:29.711
...tell people not to sleep so tight.

55:29.880 --> 55:32.440
Telling people to turn around.
Toward what?

55:32.960 --> 55:34.633
Roman, sit down.

55:34.800 --> 55:37.110
There's no need anymore.

55:37.280 --> 55:40.034
The incapacity ceases with...

55:40.200 --> 55:41.953
...the cause that produces it.

55:42.120 --> 55:43.554
Roman, he can hear you.

55:43.720 --> 55:46.076
Well, that's what I came to say.

55:46.520 --> 55:48.352
Anyway, he...

55:54.160 --> 55:55.514
Anyway, he's gone, so...

55:59.080 --> 56:00.639
What he fought for...

56:00.800 --> 56:03.713
...what he takes with him,
that lasts forever.

56:03.920 --> 56:05.639
Eroding as it was conceived.

56:06.000 --> 56:08.435
What is wrong with you?

56:09.720 --> 56:11.393
You know,
there's a shop by the ocean...

56:11.560 --> 56:13.517
...that makes maple-glazed
turkey-bacon doughnuts.

56:13.720 --> 56:15.359
People sit under palm trees
and eat them...

56:15.520 --> 56:17.398
...while the breezes are blowing
and the dolphins are playing.

56:17.600 --> 56:19.239
I'm gonna go there.

56:19.880 --> 56:21.360
Roman, all right, sit down.

56:21.560 --> 56:24.519
- No. I'm gonna get one.
- No, no, sit down.

56:24.680 --> 56:26.319
Roman.

56:27.160 --> 56:28.196
Roman.

57:52.360 --> 57:53.476
<i>Hello?</i>

57:53.640 --> 57:58.635
Hello. I'm calling in... In reference
to the, uh, deceased store clerk.

57:58.800 --> 58:00.553
<i>I'm sorry?</i>

58:01.240 --> 58:03.391
The... Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm calling in reference...

58:03.560 --> 58:06.598
...to the... The shooter
of the deceased store clerk.

58:06.760 --> 58:08.592
<i>Hold on a sec.</i>

58:13.520 --> 58:14.556
Yes, can I help you?

58:15.080 --> 58:16.992
Yes, the...

58:17.680 --> 58:20.070
The man who did it,
I know where he is.

58:20.240 --> 58:23.199
<i>- I'm ready.
- Um...</i>

58:23.520 --> 58:26.354
Well, I'm calling about the reward,
the $100,000?

58:27.240 --> 58:30.278
You know the name of the suspect?
We've had a lot of false leads.

58:30.480 --> 58:32.199
Carter T. Johnson.

58:35.320 --> 58:36.800
<i>Where is he?</i>

58:36.960 --> 58:40.954
Well, the man who did it,
uh, I have an address.

58:41.160 --> 58:43.391
<i>The clerk was my nephew.</i>

58:43.920 --> 58:47.277
Listen, I'm not comfortable, uh...

58:47.440 --> 58:50.717
...identifying myself.
I have a mechanism to collect...

58:50.920 --> 58:53.913
...which, um, protects who I am.

58:54.080 --> 58:55.753
<i>You could just say where he is.</i>

58:55.920 --> 58:57.195
<i>Civic duty.</i>

58:57.360 --> 58:59.238
<i>Basic human dignity.</i>

58:59.400 --> 59:01.357
Look, this is an achievement for me,
okay?

59:01.520 --> 59:03.477
Not an inherent state of my existence.

59:03.680 --> 59:07.833
I want the money in cash
as soon as he's arrested, $100,000.

59:08.000 --> 59:09.434
<i>Can't do cash.</i>

59:09.600 --> 59:11.080
<i>Too risky.</i>

59:11.240 --> 59:12.833
I'm the one taking the risk.

59:13.000 --> 59:15.993
It's gotta be cash. That's the way it is.

59:17.240 --> 59:18.913
Okay. Fine.

59:19.800 --> 59:22.759
<i>I don't care who you are.
I just want the bastards caught.</i>

59:22.920 --> 59:24.593
Okay. Okay.

59:24.760 --> 59:26.353
<i>The reward stands.</i>

59:26.520 --> 59:28.352
<i>- Okay.
- Information leading to an arrest.</i>

59:28.520 --> 59:30.477
<i>- Okay.
- You want cash, I'll do cash.</i>

59:31.880 --> 59:33.837
<i>Give me the information.</i>

01:03:24.960 --> 01:03:27.111
- You guys have a good day.
- Have a good one.

01:03:27.880 --> 01:03:30.395
- Good morning.
- Morning. Yes, it is. Good morning.

01:03:30.560 --> 01:03:33.473
Get three of your turkey-bacon
maple-glazed doughnuts, please.

01:03:33.640 --> 01:03:36.519
Three turkey-bacon maple.
Something to drink with that?

01:03:36.680 --> 01:03:40.594
Yes, the hibiscus-pomegranate cooler.

01:03:41.120 --> 01:03:43.032
Hibiscus-pomegranate cooler.

01:03:44.720 --> 01:03:46.279
Twelve dollars on the nose.

01:03:46.440 --> 01:03:47.920
Can you break 100?

01:03:48.080 --> 01:03:49.434
Of course.

01:03:56.560 --> 01:03:58.358
Eighty-eight back to you.

01:03:58.560 --> 01:04:00.870
- Keep the change.
- Hey, thanks.

01:04:26.280 --> 01:04:29.034
- Those fit?
- Yeah. Yeah.

01:04:29.200 --> 01:04:32.079
- You think so?
- Trust me.

01:04:32.240 --> 01:04:34.391
Can I get you anything else today, sir?

01:04:34.560 --> 01:04:35.994
A suit.

01:04:36.160 --> 01:04:37.196
Suits.

01:04:37.360 --> 01:04:39.431
Heh. Now we're talking.

01:04:44.200 --> 01:04:48.319
Loews Santa Monica Beach Hotel.
Good afternoon. How may I help you?

01:04:48.480 --> 01:04:49.834
Welcome, sir. Checking in?

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:51.639
Roman J. Israel, Esquire.

01:04:51.800 --> 01:04:53.314
- Welcome to Loews.
- Thank you.

01:07:29.960 --> 01:07:31.997
<i>- It's a very nice suit.
- Thank you.</i>

01:07:33.560 --> 01:07:36.473
Lynn went to your apartment
this weekend to speak with you...

01:07:36.640 --> 01:07:38.393
...but you weren't there.

01:07:38.560 --> 01:07:41.155
Oh, I must have been out.

01:07:42.280 --> 01:07:45.159
You... You don't know
what I'm talking about.

01:07:46.240 --> 01:07:48.197
- You're firing me?
- No.

01:07:48.840 --> 01:07:51.230
No. People became concerned
after you went to the hospital...

01:07:51.400 --> 01:07:54.279
...Friday morning, and it was decided
after some discussion...

01:07:54.440 --> 01:07:57.512
...that it was best not to leave a message
on your phone.

01:07:58.960 --> 01:08:00.235
William died.

01:08:01.320 --> 01:08:03.391
Oh. When?

01:08:04.040 --> 01:08:05.190
Friday night, actually.

01:08:06.400 --> 01:08:08.995
- I'm sorry.
- You didn't kill him.

01:08:11.280 --> 01:08:13.875
There's gonna be a small private funeral
on Wednesday...

01:08:14.040 --> 01:08:16.509
...and then a full memorial
in several weeks.

01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:17.955
Is that it?

01:08:18.120 --> 01:08:19.759
I don't know what you're feeling...

01:08:20.279 --> 01:08:22.430
...given how close you were.

01:08:22.600 --> 01:08:24.876
I mean, I guess...
I guess I can kind of imagine.

01:08:26.080 --> 01:08:28.072
Yeah. I put that behind me.

01:08:28.240 --> 01:08:31.676
Well, I'm sorry for my outburst
the other day. I was...

01:08:32.439 --> 01:08:33.920
I was overly harsh.

01:08:34.760 --> 01:08:37.639
Lynn's been telling me
how vital you were to William's work.

01:08:37.840 --> 01:08:40.071
Always in the shadows,
never flagging...

01:08:40.240 --> 01:08:44.393
...and I pulled you out of the back room and
forced you out onto the floor. It was...

01:08:45.080 --> 01:08:47.231
It was a lot to ask.

01:08:47.680 --> 01:08:49.671
I've gotten Felicity Ellerbee
to sign a document...

01:08:49.840 --> 01:08:52.877
...absolving us of any wrongdoing
in her nephew's death.

01:08:53.040 --> 01:08:55.111
It's a good thing that she...

01:08:55.279 --> 01:08:59.035
She believes that you were just acting
in Derrell's best interests.

01:08:59.200 --> 01:09:01.078
So that's in the rearview.

01:09:01.640 --> 01:09:03.518
I've also learned today
that we picked up...

01:09:03.680 --> 01:09:06.354
...three new clients, all of whom came
as referrals from your cases.

01:09:06.520 --> 01:09:09.274
It seems like your personal attention,
giving out your cell phone...

01:09:09.439 --> 01:09:10.760
...is quite the calling card.

01:09:10.920 --> 01:09:13.354
I wanna institute the practice
for all our attorneys.

01:09:13.520 --> 01:09:14.840
Good.

01:09:16.240 --> 01:09:18.037
Look, you can still leave, of course.

01:09:18.200 --> 01:09:21.796
I fully understand. I think maybe there's...
Maybe there's a place for you here if you...

01:09:21.960 --> 01:09:23.519
- I wanna stay.
- You would?

01:09:23.720 --> 01:09:24.948
Yes.

01:09:25.120 --> 01:09:28.557
I mean, I'm tired of doing
the impossible for the ungrateful.

01:09:28.720 --> 01:09:31.633
I now have, uh, more...

01:09:32.680 --> 01:09:34.990
...practical concerns.

01:09:35.439 --> 01:09:37.113
The suit's a big change.

01:09:37.880 --> 01:09:39.519
Thank you.

01:09:39.680 --> 01:09:41.876
I prefer double-breasted, but, uh...

01:09:42.040 --> 01:09:45.555
- You broke open the piggy bank, huh?
- Yeah. Yes, I did.

01:09:46.279 --> 01:09:49.398
My lack of success is self-imposed.

01:09:54.720 --> 01:09:58.555
So, Israel, there's a rumor
that you know the CPC by heart.

01:09:58.720 --> 01:10:00.154
Yeah. Guilty as charged.

01:10:00.840 --> 01:10:03.036
- Pleadings.
- Nine forty-eight, 973.

01:10:03.200 --> 01:10:04.759
- Demurrer for irregularity.
- Twelve forty-eight.

01:10:04.920 --> 01:10:05.990
Money laundering.

01:10:06.160 --> 01:10:10.916
186.9, 186.10.
However, all pleadings in those cases...

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:14.915
...are subject to the laws
of joinder and severance. That's 954.

01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:16.719
- Wow, impressive.
- Nice.

01:10:16.920 --> 01:10:20.152
Heh. You gotta be kidding me.

01:10:20.360 --> 01:10:21.714
I gotta go.

01:10:21.880 --> 01:10:23.792
See you, Jessie.

01:10:24.640 --> 01:10:27.758
Listen, um, I got a Prop 36
I could really use help with.

01:10:28.360 --> 01:10:29.555
Okay.

01:10:29.720 --> 01:10:32.110
We handled a lot of DTC motions
at my old firm.

01:10:32.280 --> 01:10:34.476
Awesome. I have some free time
this afternoon, if you do.

01:10:34.640 --> 01:10:37.314
I don't know what your caseload is like,
but I'll stop by?

01:10:37.480 --> 01:10:38.630
- Yeah.
- Great.

01:10:58.440 --> 01:11:00.796
So where do you currently live?

01:11:00.960 --> 01:11:02.838
Further away.

01:11:03.720 --> 01:11:06.076
Well, if you lived here,
you'd be home by now.

01:11:23.800 --> 01:11:25.678
Well, what do you think?

01:11:26.400 --> 01:11:29.518
I think that whatever we're chasing...

01:11:31.160 --> 01:11:33.072
...you got it all here.

01:11:33.440 --> 01:11:36.080
- I'm sorry?
- When can I move in?

01:11:36.240 --> 01:11:39.039
- Immediately.
- I'll take it.

01:12:08.160 --> 01:12:11.915
<i>- Hello?
- Oh, hey. It's, uh... It's Maya.</i>

01:12:12.480 --> 01:12:13.516
Hi.

01:12:14.120 --> 01:12:16.555
- How are you doing?
- Wonderful.

01:12:16.720 --> 01:12:18.598
Good. I, uh...

01:12:18.760 --> 01:12:21.992
I meant what I said last week
about staying in touch.

01:12:22.160 --> 01:12:24.277
How's the new job?

01:12:24.480 --> 01:12:28.190
I'm writing lengthy interrogatories...

01:12:28.840 --> 01:12:30.069
...and amending complaints.

01:12:30.280 --> 01:12:33.876
<i>It's no social-redeeming quality
or context.</i>

01:12:34.040 --> 01:12:35.793
You know, it's...

01:12:35.960 --> 01:12:37.917
It's awesome.

01:12:40.080 --> 01:12:41.400
Okay.

01:12:41.560 --> 01:12:44.792
Well, I was calling to see
if you wanted to go for dinner.

01:12:46.880 --> 01:12:47.996
With me?

01:12:48.680 --> 01:12:50.273
<i>With you?</i>

01:12:50.800 --> 01:12:52.029
I'm confused.

01:12:52.200 --> 01:12:53.953
I... I'd like that.

01:12:54.120 --> 01:12:55.634
I'd like that.

01:12:55.800 --> 01:12:58.156
<i>- I'd like that, yeah. Um...
- Great.</i>

01:13:00.160 --> 01:13:02.436
Tonight? I mean...

01:13:03.520 --> 01:13:05.034
<i>Tomorrow?</i>

01:13:05.200 --> 01:13:07.032
<i>- Works for me.
- It works for me.</i>

01:13:07.200 --> 01:13:09.840
Tonight works for me, but, I mean...

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:12.071
All right. I'll... I...

01:13:13.520 --> 01:13:16.194
Tomorrow. I'll do tomorrow.
We'll do tomorrow.

01:13:16.360 --> 01:13:19.319
Okay. I'll see you then.

01:13:19.480 --> 01:13:20.914
<i>Bye.</i>

01:13:44.920 --> 01:13:46.149
Everybody in?

01:13:53.240 --> 01:13:55.038
All right, let's get started.

01:13:55.240 --> 01:13:58.551
Under the new fee structure,
our advance on felony cases...

01:13:58.720 --> 01:14:00.677
...rises from 2000 to 2500.

01:14:01.480 --> 01:14:05.110
Our felony daily rate rises
to 1500 from 1000.

01:14:05.280 --> 01:14:08.352
Now, of course, some people are
gonna gag at the new numbers...

01:14:08.520 --> 01:14:11.638
...but what we're selling is
our impressive win-loss record...

01:14:11.840 --> 01:14:13.638
...our depth of talent,
all you fine people...

01:14:13.840 --> 01:14:16.230
...and, ultimately, our lower all-in costs.

01:14:16.400 --> 01:14:17.550
Take time to explain it.

01:14:17.760 --> 01:14:20.150
If you see a potential client heading
for the door...

01:14:20.320 --> 01:14:23.279
...you emphasize
our new personalized approach.

01:14:23.440 --> 01:14:25.511
All right, I've also decided to devote...

01:14:25.680 --> 01:14:28.240
...a share of our time to pro bono.

01:14:28.680 --> 01:14:31.240
Now, that's not an area
we have much experience with...

01:14:31.440 --> 01:14:33.352
...but someone here does.

01:14:33.520 --> 01:14:35.239
It's the first he's heard about it...

01:14:35.400 --> 01:14:39.030
...but Roman will be heading up
our new pro bono program.

01:14:39.560 --> 01:14:41.199
Roman, you want to say a few words?

01:14:43.680 --> 01:14:45.433
Will this cut into my salary?

01:14:49.360 --> 01:14:51.397
I mean, in terms of billable hours?

01:14:58.120 --> 01:15:00.237
- Okay.
- All right. Heh.

01:15:00.400 --> 01:15:03.837
Connor, you'll be assisting Roman.
I want to get moving on it right away.

01:15:04.000 --> 01:15:06.390
Folks, take a look.
It's already in the new brochure.

01:15:06.600 --> 01:15:08.432
All right, questions?

01:15:08.600 --> 01:15:10.239
Nothing? Good.

01:15:18.640 --> 01:15:21.633
- Roman, I didn't dress for this place.
- Oh, there's no code.

01:15:21.800 --> 01:15:23.632
It's a bit uncomfortable for me.

01:15:23.800 --> 01:15:25.075
You don't like it?

01:15:25.240 --> 01:15:27.550
This will cost a fortune.

01:15:27.880 --> 01:15:29.030
Well...

01:15:29.200 --> 01:15:31.510
Yeah. We deserve it.

01:15:31.720 --> 01:15:33.996
You know,
I really heard what you said...

01:15:34.160 --> 01:15:36.038
...the first time you came in.

01:15:36.200 --> 01:15:40.672
About progressive lawyering being
the cornerstone of modern activism.

01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:46.314
Particularly given the tunnel
that we're descending into.

01:15:46.920 --> 01:15:49.071
You, the few lawyers like you...

01:15:49.240 --> 01:15:50.913
Thank you.

01:15:51.520 --> 01:15:55.878
You really took up the mantle
of leadership with your own advocacy.

01:15:56.360 --> 01:15:58.158
You're out there...

01:15:58.360 --> 01:16:00.875
...and alone for so many years.

01:16:01.760 --> 01:16:03.592
I feel like...

01:16:04.960 --> 01:16:07.555
I don't know.
I feel like I was meant to meet you.

01:16:08.960 --> 01:16:09.996
Ah.

01:16:17.640 --> 01:16:19.518
- Thank you.
- I've been going through...

01:16:19.720 --> 01:16:21.040
...my own struggles.

01:16:21.760 --> 01:16:25.231
You know, trying to balance what I do...

01:16:26.640 --> 01:16:28.996
...and the sacrifices.

01:16:30.360 --> 01:16:32.716
I've asked myself many times,
"Why do I see things...

01:16:32.880 --> 01:16:35.270
...so differently from other people?"

01:16:36.640 --> 01:16:38.518
You know, why...?

01:16:39.920 --> 01:16:43.994
Why do I care so much that our humanity
is connected to each other?

01:16:46.560 --> 01:16:48.836
I have moments...

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:55.710
I have extended periods of real doubt.

01:16:57.040 --> 01:16:58.838
I'm just holding on by a thread.

01:17:02.920 --> 01:17:04.798
So, uh...

01:17:04.960 --> 01:17:06.952
...hearing you...

01:17:07.120 --> 01:17:10.511
...and, um, understanding
what you've been through...

01:17:11.960 --> 01:17:14.077
...and... Thank you.

01:17:16.280 --> 01:17:18.636
Just knowing you.

01:17:19.600 --> 01:17:23.799
I mean, honestly,
Roman, you're inspiring.

01:17:28.520 --> 01:17:29.749
I've never had it before...

01:17:31.040 --> 01:17:34.078
...but I imagined Duck à l'Orange
to be different somehow.

01:17:36.600 --> 01:17:38.000
Jesus, I'm being serious.

01:17:38.160 --> 01:17:42.712
Perhaps you need to look
at things differently. You all right?

01:17:42.880 --> 01:17:45.714
- How?
- Well...

01:17:47.600 --> 01:17:51.071
...the world is for wonderful things,
isn't it?

01:17:52.160 --> 01:17:54.516
Define "wonderful."

01:17:55.280 --> 01:17:57.749
Okay. As an example...

01:17:58.520 --> 01:18:00.352
...who says...

01:18:00.840 --> 01:18:02.752
...you can't steal a car in self-defense?

01:18:02.920 --> 01:18:04.115
In reference to what?

01:18:04.320 --> 01:18:09.076
If one required a means of escape,
so to speak.

01:18:09.240 --> 01:18:10.879
Escape from what?

01:18:11.080 --> 01:18:15.393
Possibility to actuality.

01:18:15.920 --> 01:18:19.960
I mean, it follows. The logic is valid,
thus the premise is true.

01:18:20.120 --> 01:18:24.080
Every weapon is a tool
if you hold it the right way.

01:18:24.240 --> 01:18:25.879
You're saying to justify something?

01:18:26.040 --> 01:18:28.032
I'm saying...

01:18:29.800 --> 01:18:31.678
...purity...

01:18:33.120 --> 01:18:35.555
...can't survive in this world.

01:18:38.760 --> 01:18:41.480
Living conditions have bearing.

01:18:42.720 --> 01:18:45.474
I'm talking about the burden of activism.

01:18:45.640 --> 01:18:46.960
Exactly.

01:18:47.120 --> 01:18:49.271
What are you talking about?

01:18:53.600 --> 01:18:55.671
My ears are ringing.

01:18:56.120 --> 01:18:58.077
It's somebody's phone.

01:18:59.680 --> 01:19:01.433
Roman.

01:19:07.200 --> 01:19:09.999
It's very difficult to be truthful.

01:19:11.320 --> 01:19:13.551
Not just with principles...

01:19:13.720 --> 01:19:14.949
...but with yourself.

01:19:15.120 --> 01:19:18.511
To admit that you want something else
and to try and act on it.

01:19:18.680 --> 01:19:21.275
But I don't want something else.

01:19:21.480 --> 01:19:25.440
I feel blessed to believe in something.

01:19:25.920 --> 01:19:27.798
The way you do.

01:19:34.320 --> 01:19:36.232
Thanks for dinner.
That was very generous.

01:19:36.400 --> 01:19:38.835
The portions were small.

01:19:39.200 --> 01:19:43.991
I'm moving into a new place
in a few days, after 35 years.

01:19:44.160 --> 01:19:48.040
- You're going through a lot of changes.
- Yeah. Yeah.

01:19:48.200 --> 01:19:51.557
- Kind of worried I'll miss my old place.
- Maybe you should wait until you're sure.

01:19:51.760 --> 01:19:54.434
Nah, signed the contract.
I can't go back.

01:19:54.640 --> 01:19:57.553
- I called a car.
- Already got you one.

01:19:57.720 --> 01:20:01.031
See, I can Uber and text. It's right here.

01:20:03.920 --> 01:20:06.276
- Thanks again.
- You're welcome.

01:20:08.800 --> 01:20:11.918
I just want you to know
how much you've helped me...

01:20:12.080 --> 01:20:14.390
...by, uh, meeting you.

01:20:14.560 --> 01:20:16.392
For what you do.

01:20:21.400 --> 01:20:24.199
- Your hair looks great.
- Thank you.

01:20:50.360 --> 01:20:53.558
William lived on grand notions...

01:20:53.720 --> 01:20:57.236
...influenced by impractical ideas...

01:20:57.680 --> 01:21:02.550
...in a house trembling with promise
and shouts of triumphs yet to come.

01:21:03.160 --> 01:21:06.232
Imploring and inspiring.

01:21:07.120 --> 01:21:10.830
A believer that the moral arc
of the universe is long...

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:13.595
...but bends towards justice.

01:21:13.800 --> 01:21:18.272
He ignited a spark
in each and every one of us...

01:21:19.200 --> 01:21:22.637
...and that light can never die.

01:21:25.520 --> 01:21:27.751
We have over 1000 attending
the memorial.

01:21:27.920 --> 01:21:31.630
Yeah, and not one of them returned
his calls when he was alive.

01:21:31.800 --> 01:21:33.871
I think it would be great if you spoke.

01:21:34.040 --> 01:21:35.872
Heh. And tell them what?

01:21:36.040 --> 01:21:39.351
- You two talk the same language.
- Yeah, no, thank you.

01:21:39.520 --> 01:21:41.318
- If it's nerves...
- It's not.

01:21:42.480 --> 01:21:45.200
- There's no one more deserving.
- They wouldn't wanna hear it.

01:21:45.360 --> 01:21:46.476
Hear what?

01:21:46.640 --> 01:21:49.951
The real enemies aren't on
the outside. They're within.

01:21:53.360 --> 01:21:55.033
We'll talk soon.

01:21:55.200 --> 01:21:56.520
I'll call you.

01:21:59.640 --> 01:22:01.552
You take care of yourself.

01:22:01.720 --> 01:22:02.870
I am.

01:22:03.760 --> 01:22:05.911
I disbelieve that.

01:22:09.000 --> 01:22:10.480
I'll be in touch.

01:22:11.320 --> 01:22:13.152
Roman, I'll see you at the office.

01:22:14.280 --> 01:22:16.476
I have something for you.

01:22:28.720 --> 01:22:32.350
No, you're right.
That 2500 is higher than average.

01:22:32.520 --> 01:22:35.399
But let me direct you
to our firm's win-loss record...

01:22:35.560 --> 01:22:38.519
...our lower all-in costs,
personalized service.

01:22:38.720 --> 01:22:42.191
- It's all there in the brochure.
- I don't know.

01:22:42.760 --> 01:22:45.116
You're wise to price shop.
Very, very wise.

01:22:45.280 --> 01:22:47.317
When it comes to defending
your loved ones...

01:22:47.520 --> 01:22:51.230
...there's a lot of people in prison
that would attest that that's a bad idea.

01:23:02.080 --> 01:23:03.799
We're going to do it.

01:23:05.600 --> 01:23:07.080
Okay.

01:23:18.400 --> 01:23:21.279
<i>Tickets for this week's game...</i>

01:23:21.440 --> 01:23:24.797
<i>...available now on the main concourse,
right behind Aisle 14.</i>

01:23:24.960 --> 01:23:26.872
Man, you've had
some crash course, huh?

01:23:27.800 --> 01:23:30.793
From William Henry Jackson
to George Pierce?

01:23:31.680 --> 01:23:33.433
What a ride.

01:23:33.840 --> 01:23:35.354
You seem to be settling in okay.

01:23:35.840 --> 01:23:37.115
From all appearances.

01:23:38.480 --> 01:23:39.880
I got a lot of plans, Roman.

01:23:40.040 --> 01:23:43.511
I mean, nothing we have to get
too deep into here, understand...

01:23:43.680 --> 01:23:46.354
...but down the line,
there is a lot I'd like to discuss.

01:23:46.520 --> 01:23:50.070
I'm gonna want your thoughts.
You know, closer community contact...

01:23:50.840 --> 01:23:53.150
...taking on more family
and housing cases...

01:23:53.320 --> 01:23:55.516
...setting up alternative
work arrangements.

01:23:55.680 --> 01:23:58.912
All while actually increasing
productivity and retention...

01:23:59.080 --> 01:24:01.549
...which is not to suggest
it's about drumming up business.

01:24:01.760 --> 01:24:04.639
I mean, something's gotta get you up
in the morning, right?

01:24:06.840 --> 01:24:08.832
And going back to William Henry...

01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:11.151
...I told you I remember quotes
from his class.

01:24:11.320 --> 01:24:15.360
"I believe because of my beliefs."

01:24:16.680 --> 01:24:19.240
I was gonna leave law...

01:24:19.400 --> 01:24:22.916
...before I took his class.
After him, I doubled down.

01:24:23.120 --> 01:24:25.954
You know, all his talk of what could be
and the difference...

01:24:26.160 --> 01:24:27.753
...one man could make.
But then you gotta make a living.

01:24:27.920 --> 01:24:29.957
Four offices, this market?

01:24:30.360 --> 01:24:33.478
It's... It's no small thing.

01:24:33.640 --> 01:24:36.712
Of course, he didn't see it that way.
He told me I was, uh...

01:24:36.920 --> 01:24:39.355
I was drowning in the shallow end.

01:24:41.480 --> 01:24:44.951
Worse was, I knew it.

01:24:45.760 --> 01:24:47.399
And then you come along, you...

01:24:47.600 --> 01:24:49.637
You shake things up a bit,
and here we are sitting...

01:24:49.800 --> 01:24:52.520
...talking new possibilities,
where we can go.

01:24:53.120 --> 01:24:55.237
Hell, I don't have to explain. You get it.

01:24:55.440 --> 01:24:57.796
Christ, you're gonna be
right in the middle of it.

01:25:40.640 --> 01:25:43.109
- Come on, man.
- That's bullshit.

01:25:47.640 --> 01:25:50.553
Whoo. L. A. traffic, man,
there's no getting around it.

01:25:50.720 --> 01:25:52.439
Glad I caught you before we came in.
We just landed this.

01:25:52.600 --> 01:25:54.592
It's a capital case.
You have experience with those?

01:25:54.760 --> 01:25:56.035
We handled quite a few.

01:25:56.200 --> 01:25:59.034
I'll make the introduction,
then I'll bow out and you'll stay.

01:25:59.200 --> 01:26:00.395
Okay.

01:26:00.560 --> 01:26:03.598
I looked at that prison-overcrowding case
you and William worked on.

01:26:03.800 --> 01:26:05.996
- Which one?
- This one was against Men's Central.

01:26:06.160 --> 01:26:08.516
- You prevailed.
- Oh, that was overturned.

01:26:08.720 --> 01:26:10.154
Yeah?

01:26:10.320 --> 01:26:12.960
- How's your big plea-reform brief going?
- Uh...

01:26:14.240 --> 01:26:15.310
Put it aside.

01:26:15.520 --> 01:26:17.637
Well, tell me more about it.
I'm interested.

01:26:18.360 --> 01:26:20.955
Carried it as far as I can take it.

01:26:21.120 --> 01:26:23.919
Well, how about some help?
I mean, I've been thinking about it.

01:26:24.080 --> 01:26:26.117
I've become less skeptical
about the possibilities...

01:26:26.320 --> 01:26:28.835
...and scope of what you said.
I could devote office resources...

01:26:29.000 --> 01:26:31.595
...help you complete the brief. We could
file it at the federal court together.

01:26:31.760 --> 01:26:34.878
That's the first step. It'll take years
of commitment to see it through.

01:26:35.080 --> 01:26:37.470
Commitment doesn't seem
to be a problem for you.

01:26:37.640 --> 01:26:39.359
I hear you're moving
to a new apartment.

01:26:39.520 --> 01:26:41.671
- How'd you hear that?
- Payroll check comes across my desk.

01:26:41.880 --> 01:26:44.600
- I know that building. It's not cheap.
- I had money saved.

01:26:44.800 --> 01:26:46.712
I mean, it's great. It's a nice building.

01:26:46.880 --> 01:26:49.156
No, I mean,
I had money saved for a long time.

01:26:49.320 --> 01:26:51.312
- Well, what else is it good for?
- Heh.

01:26:51.480 --> 01:26:53.199
- You got your ID?
- Yeah, yeah.

01:26:53.720 --> 01:26:57.430
George Pierce and Roman Israel
to see our client, Carter Johnson.

01:26:57.600 --> 01:26:59.478
- Carter Johnson?
- I meant to tell you.

01:26:59.640 --> 01:27:01.996
They picked him up on Friday
from the Ellerbee case.

01:27:02.160 --> 01:27:03.310
We've been retained.

01:27:29.680 --> 01:27:31.433
Hello, Carter.

01:27:31.640 --> 01:27:34.235
I'm George Pierce, and this is
my associate Roman Israel.

01:27:34.400 --> 01:27:36.790
Roman is a devoted advocate
and a fabulous attorney.

01:27:36.960 --> 01:27:39.680
And he's gonna be
the point person on your team.

01:27:40.280 --> 01:27:42.920
- You're good, huh?
- Well, he's better than good.

01:27:43.080 --> 01:27:45.436
Have you had a chance
to review the fee structure?

01:27:45.600 --> 01:27:47.512
- The stuff you sent over? Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:27:47.680 --> 01:27:49.080
You understand this is
a capital murder case?

01:27:49.640 --> 01:27:51.313
- Yeah.
- All right, first off...

01:27:51.480 --> 01:27:53.312
...you wanna be fully up to speed
on your file.

01:27:53.480 --> 01:27:56.154
You will make better decisions
if you're completely informed...

01:27:56.320 --> 01:27:58.835
...about every aspect of your case
and you know all your options.

01:27:59.040 --> 01:28:00.997
I know all my options.

01:28:01.160 --> 01:28:04.597
Well, unfortunately, we, uh,
can't change what's been done.

01:28:04.800 --> 01:28:07.110
That means facing this head-on.

01:28:07.280 --> 01:28:10.352
I think you understand the penalties
you're facing are very severe.

01:28:11.160 --> 01:28:13.436
In overview,
we're gonna study the discovery...

01:28:13.640 --> 01:28:15.313
...of the evidence
the prosecution gives us.

01:28:15.480 --> 01:28:17.153
And we're gonna force the prosecution...

01:28:17.320 --> 01:28:19.118
...to give us anything
and everything we want.

01:28:19.280 --> 01:28:21.237
- Roman, you wanna step in?
- Yeah, we're gonna...

01:28:21.440 --> 01:28:25.514
We're gonna perform
a private investigation...

01:28:26.160 --> 01:28:27.594
...and devise a defense.

01:28:28.040 --> 01:28:30.714
That's not all we'll do.
We'll outwork the prosecution.

01:28:30.880 --> 01:28:33.918
All right? We're gonna outwork them,
we're gonna outperform them.

01:28:34.120 --> 01:28:36.760
And we're gonna get you
the best result possible.

01:28:36.920 --> 01:28:40.197
- Life in a cage.
- Well, that's the outcome we're fighting.

01:28:40.760 --> 01:28:43.400
It'll be a long process,
and it's gonna cost quite a bit.

01:28:43.560 --> 01:28:44.914
So with that in mind, I...

01:28:45.080 --> 01:28:47.595
I'd like to suggest there's no need
for two billable attorneys...

01:28:47.800 --> 01:28:51.510
...at this early phase. If it's okay with
you, I'll bow out. I'll let Roman continue.

01:28:52.680 --> 01:28:54.319
It's okay with me.

01:28:54.480 --> 01:28:56.233
All right, Carter.

01:28:56.600 --> 01:28:58.557
I'll be in touch.

01:28:58.720 --> 01:29:01.189
- Roman, I'll speak with you later.
- Okay.

01:29:01.360 --> 01:29:02.953
Guard.

01:29:06.200 --> 01:29:07.236
The, um...

01:29:09.600 --> 01:29:11.034
Um...

01:29:11.520 --> 01:29:14.718
The prosecutors are gonna favor
a grand jury...

01:29:14.880 --> 01:29:19.352
...over a preliminary hearing,
which will allow them to wait...

01:29:19.520 --> 01:29:22.752
- ...and reveal the evidence at the trial.
- You represented Derrell.

01:29:23.840 --> 01:29:25.399
Briefly.

01:29:26.040 --> 01:29:29.158
I asked for you
after talking to his cellie.

01:29:30.960 --> 01:29:33.395
We have a number
of legal maneuvers we can employ...

01:29:33.920 --> 01:29:35.639
...to try and force a prelim.

01:29:35.800 --> 01:29:38.872
- I don't care about the prelim.
- I'd advise that we pursue it.

01:29:39.360 --> 01:29:41.920
You knew where I was.

01:29:42.080 --> 01:29:43.309
When was that?

01:29:43.520 --> 01:29:44.795
Before they picked me up.

01:29:44.960 --> 01:29:47.555
I'm sure Derrell shared that info
with a number of people.

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:49.559
No.

01:29:50.000 --> 01:29:51.673
You're the only person he told.

01:29:52.520 --> 01:29:54.876
That's what he told the guy.

01:29:55.040 --> 01:29:58.556
You called it in,
collected the reward money.

01:29:58.960 --> 01:30:02.874
- You fucked me.
- I presented myself...

01:30:03.080 --> 01:30:05.675
...on your request for an attorney.

01:30:05.840 --> 01:30:09.436
You're talking,
but it don't mean nothing.

01:30:10.080 --> 01:30:12.197
I ain't never getting out of here.

01:30:12.360 --> 01:30:14.636
They got me cold.

01:30:15.040 --> 01:30:17.236
But I'll tell you this.

01:30:18.240 --> 01:30:20.197
I got you.

01:30:20.640 --> 01:30:21.915
Anytime I want.

01:30:22.080 --> 01:30:23.560
- Guard... Guard.
- Any place.

01:30:23.720 --> 01:30:25.598
- Guard!
- Could've already done it.

01:30:25.760 --> 01:30:27.717
- Guard.
- But I want you to be where I am.

01:30:27.880 --> 01:30:29.599
- Guard!
- Thinking about it.

01:30:29.760 --> 01:30:32.355
- Guard.
- Go on and tell somebody what you did.

01:30:32.520 --> 01:30:34.352
- I want out.
- Broke your own law.

01:30:34.520 --> 01:30:36.113
- Privileged information.
- Guard!

01:30:36.320 --> 01:30:40.109
Tell them about the law you broke.
They'll throw you in here with me.

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:43.879
What, you gonna run? Try it.

01:31:38.200 --> 01:31:39.270
Hello?

01:31:42.160 --> 01:31:43.640
Hello?

01:31:49.960 --> 01:31:53.636
<i>- Front desk.
- Yes, I just received a call, uh...</i>

01:31:53.800 --> 01:31:56.838
<i>- There was no one there.
- Well, they asked for you, Mr. Israel.</i>

01:31:57.000 --> 01:31:58.514
Did they give a name?

01:31:58.680 --> 01:32:00.990
<i>I'm sorry. No, they didn't.</i>

01:32:45.840 --> 01:32:47.593
Hello?

01:37:27.600 --> 01:37:29.034
H ey!

01:37:31.680 --> 01:37:32.670
Hey, you okay?

01:37:35.600 --> 01:37:36.750
You all right, mister?

01:37:41.440 --> 01:37:43.397
I was running.

01:37:43.920 --> 01:37:45.957
You need any help?

01:37:46.480 --> 01:37:47.960
It was a bad decision.

01:37:49.160 --> 01:37:51.595
- It wasn't my first.
- Dude's crazy.

01:37:54.480 --> 01:37:55.516
Come on.

01:38:21.200 --> 01:38:23.954
<i>- Hello?
- Hey. It's Maya.</i>

01:38:24.120 --> 01:38:26.760
<i>- Hi, Maya.
- What are you doing?</i>

01:38:26.960 --> 01:38:28.519
Uh...

01:38:28.760 --> 01:38:31.992
<i>- Nothing much.
- You'd tell me if I was bugging you.</i>

01:38:32.160 --> 01:38:34.072
<i>- No.
- Heh-heh.</i>

01:38:34.240 --> 01:38:35.515
<i>Well, that's honest.</i>

01:38:35.720 --> 01:38:39.999
<i>You know I only call you
when I'm down. That's horrible, right?</i>

01:38:40.160 --> 01:38:42.038
<i>One of my friends...</i>

01:38:42.200 --> 01:38:44.590
<i>One of my best staffers
quit on me yesterday.</i>

01:38:44.760 --> 01:38:47.434
<i>Told me that working here
was just for his résumé.</i>

01:38:47.600 --> 01:38:50.160
Oh. The ability to have...

01:38:50.360 --> 01:38:53.398
...conflicting ideas
in one's head takes effort.

01:38:53.560 --> 01:38:55.438
<i>Huh. I like that.</i>

01:38:55.600 --> 01:38:57.080
<i>How's your day going?</i>

01:38:57.280 --> 01:38:58.919
Oh, you know...

01:38:59.120 --> 01:39:01.760
<i>- ...life smiles, I smile back.
- Heh.</i>

01:39:01.920 --> 01:39:05.311
<i>- You don't sound like you're smiling.
- I'm a little...</i>

01:39:05.480 --> 01:39:08.473
<i>- Kind of anxious, actually.
- Well, just tell yourself...</i>

01:39:08.640 --> 01:39:11.951
<i>...that most of the things you worry about
will never, ever happen.</i>

01:39:12.120 --> 01:39:14.999
<i>- I'll try that.
- Alcohol works even better. Heh.</i>

01:39:16.360 --> 01:39:17.680
<i>- Roman?
- Yeah.</i>

01:39:17.840 --> 01:39:20.230
<i>It's a really bad connection.
Where are you?</i>

01:39:20.400 --> 01:39:22.312
In a desert.

01:39:22.480 --> 01:39:25.359
<i>Yeah, it feels like that sometimes.</i>

01:39:25.760 --> 01:39:27.353
<i>Just gotta keep moving.</i>

01:39:27.560 --> 01:39:29.199
Well, which way?

01:39:29.400 --> 01:39:32.154
<i>Head on. Just straight through. Heh.</i>

01:39:33.560 --> 01:39:35.756
<i>- Hello?
- Roman?</i>

01:39:36.080 --> 01:39:38.515
<i>- Hey, can you hear...?
- Hello?</i>

01:39:38.680 --> 01:39:40.273
Maya?

01:40:34.000 --> 01:40:36.117
<i>As social action
affects the course of law...</i>

01:40:36.280 --> 01:40:38.192
<i>...let's call to account
the original complaint.</i>

01:40:38.360 --> 01:40:40.829
<i>We're agents of change,
united by virtue...</i>

01:40:41.000 --> 01:40:44.516
<i>Wrongs will be righted. A loophole
of ambiguity in the system...</i>

01:40:44.720 --> 01:40:46.598
<i>Legal challenge
based on improvement...</i>

01:40:46.760 --> 01:40:49.355
<i>Revised draft of a new community
unevenly applied...</i>

01:40:49.560 --> 01:40:52.314
<i>For a verdict of history,
formally empowered with authority.</i>

01:40:52.520 --> 01:40:55.479
<i>- -levers of the law. There needs
to be a bottom-up legal change.</i>

01:40:55.640 --> 01:40:58.314
<i>Who'll see us?
What the world could be, not what it is.</i>

01:40:58.480 --> 01:41:00.551
<i>Society is something to be invented,
not endured.</i>

01:41:00.720 --> 01:41:02.837
<i>...must stand, or go down together.</i>

01:41:04.840 --> 01:41:06.433
Hey, Roman.

01:41:07.080 --> 01:41:08.514
What are you doing?

01:41:42.200 --> 01:41:45.591
<i>Case 00-001.</i>

01:41:54.800 --> 01:41:57.360
<i>versus himself, defendant.</i>

01:42:14.520 --> 01:42:15.874
Hey.

01:42:16.040 --> 01:42:19.636
I just heard something disturbing
about you from a solid source.

01:42:19.800 --> 01:42:22.713
About the Ellerbee case.
Carter Johnson?

01:42:22.880 --> 01:42:25.395
You collected the reward?

01:42:26.240 --> 01:42:28.630
<i>- Is that true?
- ... in the city of Los Angeles.</i>

01:42:28.800 --> 01:42:31.520
<i>- During that time...
- Roman.</i>

01:42:37.880 --> 01:42:39.917
<i>for the above-mentioned request...</i>

01:42:40.080 --> 01:42:43.551
<i>...for immediate and summaryjudgment.</i>

01:42:49.200 --> 01:42:50.680
I thought we were working tonight.

01:42:50.840 --> 01:42:54.277
- Uh... I plan to leave.
- Monday, then? Tomorrow?

01:42:54.480 --> 01:42:57.837
I believe I'll be unavailable
for the foreseeable future.

01:42:58.000 --> 01:42:59.673
You know the facts.

01:42:59.840 --> 01:43:01.593
- Just jump in.
- You mean, on my own?

01:43:01.760 --> 01:43:02.876
You got it.

01:43:16.400 --> 01:43:19.199
<i>- Did you check his office?
- That's what I'm saying, he left.</i>

01:43:19.360 --> 01:43:21.238
<i>- When?
- A few minutes ago.</i>

01:43:21.400 --> 01:43:22.959
Goddamn it,
he's not answering his cell.

01:43:23.120 --> 01:43:26.352
Just keep trying him
and let me know, all right?

01:43:32.080 --> 01:43:34.311
Roman. Roman!

01:44:03.760 --> 01:44:06.798
- Okay.
- Yeah, I'm back. Heh-heh.

01:44:08.280 --> 01:44:12.194
- What is that?
- That's for you.

01:44:12.360 --> 01:44:14.397
- It's a bulldog.
- Amongst other things.

01:44:14.600 --> 01:44:17.718
- It's so real.
- It actually is alive.

01:44:18.520 --> 01:44:19.954
Why are you giving it to me?

01:44:20.800 --> 01:44:22.757
To take care of.

01:44:23.800 --> 01:44:26.952
- Heh. You're a trip.
- Well...

01:44:27.120 --> 01:44:29.191
...you're worth having in this thing.

01:44:29.360 --> 01:44:32.432
Here. Put it up here.

01:44:32.600 --> 01:44:34.273
- Is it yours?
- For a while.

01:44:34.440 --> 01:44:37.717
- Well, then you should keep it, Roman.
- Well, I don't have room.

01:44:37.880 --> 01:44:39.758
- In your apartment.
- I gave it up.

01:44:39.960 --> 01:44:41.155
Why?

01:44:41.320 --> 01:44:43.789
- I'm going away.
- Where?

01:44:44.240 --> 01:44:47.995
Wherever they send me. See,
something has occurred. Something...

01:44:48.760 --> 01:44:51.275
I've just taken a career
which was certainly sincere and...

01:44:51.440 --> 01:44:53.397
And well-intentioned
and launched it right into...

01:44:53.560 --> 01:44:55.870
...the realm
of the truly transformational.

01:44:56.040 --> 01:44:58.680
I promise you that the attorney
that triumphs in this instance...

01:44:58.840 --> 01:45:01.992
...won't be the one with the most
formal education or legal skill.

01:45:02.160 --> 01:45:03.992
Roman, what are you talking about?

01:45:04.160 --> 01:45:06.516
Well, it's quite interesting, actually.

01:45:06.680 --> 01:45:08.273
- There you are.
- Hey, George.

01:45:08.440 --> 01:45:10.909
- This is Maya. Maya, this is George.
- Hey.

01:45:11.080 --> 01:45:12.992
- Hello.
- Maya...

01:45:13.200 --> 01:45:14.680
...doesn't...

01:45:14.840 --> 01:45:18.629
...overlook the vital things...

01:45:18.800 --> 01:45:20.473
...like other people.

01:45:21.880 --> 01:45:24.076
And speaking for myself,
I'm thankful for that.

01:45:24.800 --> 01:45:27.872
Roman tells me
that he really enjoys working for you.

01:45:28.280 --> 01:45:30.920
Yeah. George is a protector of rights.
That's truth...

01:45:31.080 --> 01:45:33.197
- ...in advertising.
- I...

01:45:33.360 --> 01:45:36.239
I need to, uh... I need to have a word
with you. Can we...?

01:45:36.400 --> 01:45:38.676
- I was leaving anyway.
- You just got here.

01:45:38.840 --> 01:45:40.240
Sorry, Maya, it's, uh...

01:45:41.120 --> 01:45:42.600
It's important.

01:45:42.760 --> 01:45:44.911
This is funny. Just to think...

01:45:46.440 --> 01:45:49.080
Three Mondays ago,
I didn't know either one of you.

01:45:49.280 --> 01:45:51.511
- Roman, I'm concerned about you.
- It's okay.

01:45:51.680 --> 01:45:53.399
George and I just need to...

01:45:53.560 --> 01:45:57.190
- ...talk business matters.
- Yeah.

01:45:58.960 --> 01:46:00.997
I believe...

01:46:01.440 --> 01:46:03.750
...the two of you are gonna...

01:46:04.440 --> 01:46:06.636
...get along very well.

01:46:08.880 --> 01:46:10.553
Roman...

01:46:16.760 --> 01:46:18.080
Roman.

01:46:18.680 --> 01:46:20.637
Roman, wait.

01:46:29.640 --> 01:46:31.313
Roman...

01:46:31.480 --> 01:46:33.437
...what the hell is going on?

01:46:33.960 --> 01:46:35.394
From my point of view?

01:46:35.560 --> 01:46:38.200
I get a call from Fritz.
Says he has reliable information...

01:46:38.360 --> 01:46:41.034
...that you turned in Carter Johnson
and collected the reward.

01:46:41.200 --> 01:46:44.159
- Here's what the prosecutor won't tell you.
- Jesus Christ, it's true.

01:46:44.320 --> 01:46:45.595
I've been given a gift, George.

01:46:45.760 --> 01:46:48.673
No, you acted utterly improperly.
I mean, you broke the law.

01:46:48.880 --> 01:46:51.270
- It so wasn't a gift, Roman.
- I'm not talking about the money.

01:46:51.440 --> 01:46:54.000
I don't care about the money,
fruit of the poisonous tree.

01:46:54.160 --> 01:46:55.879
If you wanna understand
what's happening...

01:46:56.040 --> 01:46:59.272
...you're gonna have to get past
all the smoke of legal disputation.

01:46:59.440 --> 01:47:02.274
Legal disputation?
Roman, these are dangerous people.

01:47:02.440 --> 01:47:06.354
- You don't just walk away from this.
- Not walking away.

01:47:06.560 --> 01:47:09.519
I'm turning myself in.
The station's on Sixth.

01:47:14.080 --> 01:47:15.594
Roman.

01:47:19.680 --> 01:47:21.911
I'll... I'll walk with you.

01:47:26.560 --> 01:47:29.473
You know,
all those years of practicing...

01:47:29.640 --> 01:47:32.394
...scouring law books...

01:47:32.560 --> 01:47:36.839
...achieving technical triumphs
through loopholes and ambiguities...

01:47:37.000 --> 01:47:38.992
...none of which were adequate
to save me...

01:47:39.160 --> 01:47:42.870
...from the reality of my present situation.
Then today, in the middle of nowhere...

01:47:43.040 --> 01:47:46.033
...lost, had a revelation.

01:47:46.200 --> 01:47:50.194
An insight so sweeping, so clear.

01:47:50.680 --> 01:47:52.433
It's me, George.

01:47:52.600 --> 01:47:56.150
See, I didn't see it before because
I never experienced the other side.

01:47:56.360 --> 01:47:57.953
I'm the defendant...

01:47:58.120 --> 01:48:00.999
...and the plaintiff simultaneously.
I file against myself...

01:48:01.200 --> 01:48:04.876
...I represent myself, I convict myself,
hereby expanding...

01:48:05.080 --> 01:48:07.879
...the full scope of the legal desert,
because the judgment's built in.

01:48:08.080 --> 01:48:12.393
The only thing left is forgiveness,
and I grant that to myself.

01:48:13.160 --> 01:48:17.837
An act doesn't make the person guilty
unless the mind is guilty as well.

01:48:20.080 --> 01:48:23.073
Of course... Of course I expect
there'll be challenges...

01:48:23.240 --> 01:48:25.550
...as there's no precedent...

01:48:25.720 --> 01:48:28.474
...or derivative interpretations...

01:48:28.640 --> 01:48:31.678
...but the argument is sound.

01:48:33.200 --> 01:48:36.910
The premise true. I have no doubt it'll
be upheld by any and all courts of law.

01:48:37.080 --> 01:48:38.833
You're insane.

01:48:39.760 --> 01:48:42.275
- Never been more clear.
- That's what we'll argue.

01:48:42.440 --> 01:48:43.556
Now, watch what you say.

01:48:43.720 --> 01:48:46.872
You don't represent me, so the rules
of confidentiality don't apply.

01:48:47.360 --> 01:48:52.037
My entire defense will be based on
the unequivocal recitation of the truth.

01:48:56.400 --> 01:48:58.835
I know you get it, George.

01:49:01.160 --> 01:49:04.198
You have such a tremendous future.
It's so bright, I...

01:49:04.360 --> 01:49:06.352
I swear, it's...

01:49:06.880 --> 01:49:09.349
Heh. It's blinding.

01:49:12.680 --> 01:49:14.512
Jesus.

01:50:41.400 --> 01:50:42.880
Hello?

01:50:49.560 --> 01:50:53.076
Of course I remember you,
that's why I gave you my card.

01:51:59.960 --> 01:52:02.475
I... I like the idea
of starting the conversation...

01:52:02.640 --> 01:52:06.270
...with how protest is
still relevant or not...

01:52:06.440 --> 01:52:12.630
...because, you know, we approach these
things with, um, a certain tradition...

01:52:12.800 --> 01:52:17.033
...a certain, you know, uh,
repetition of behavior...

01:52:17.200 --> 01:52:21.274
...and sometimes thinking through it,
we have to find new approaches.

01:52:31.640 --> 01:52:33.313
<i>To whom it may concern...</i>

01:52:33.920 --> 01:52:36.230
<i>...I'm returning the reward money.</i>

01:52:36.400 --> 01:52:40.633
<i>Taking it was wrong, and I'm compelled
to remedy my mistake.</i>

01:52:40.800 --> 01:52:46.910
<i>I did spend $5,547.27,
which I will repay.</i>

01:52:47.080 --> 01:52:50.676
<i>I bought three suits, size 50 regular.</i>

01:52:50.840 --> 01:52:54.151
<i>And I did buy two pairs
of Italian loafers, size 11.</i>

01:52:54.320 --> 01:52:57.472
<i>One black, one brown.</i>

01:52:59.240 --> 01:53:01.596
<i>We are all formed of frailty...</i>

01:53:01.760 --> 01:53:03.353
<i>...and error.</i>

01:53:03.520 --> 01:53:06.319
<i>Let us pardon, reciprocally...</i>

01:53:06.480 --> 01:53:08.278
<i>...each other's folly.</i>

01:53:09.040 --> 01:53:11.475
<i>That is the first law...</i>

01:53:11.680 --> 01:53:13.399
<i>...of nature.</i>

01:54:00.360 --> 01:54:03.080
I'm filing a federal
brief in District Nine.

